dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from an email sent by the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. The geometry was updated by cleaning its attributes and topology. The layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS:
1. Created and populated admin 0 pcode field. Admin 0 p-code is "SD". 2. Created and populated admin 0 name field. Admin 0 name is "Sudan". 3. Created and populated a reference name field. 4. Fixed 351 gap errors and 87 overlap errors in geometry. 5. "Abyei PCA Area" is now represented in the admin 1 boundaries. Its admin 1 p-code is "SD19".
The following comes from the COD Registry splash page for SUDAN: Admin Level 1 Boundaries:
"Most Recent Changes: The state boundaries are adjusted to match the international boundaries. The two Kordofan states have changed into three Kordofan states (North, South and West)"
